rce/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chiles, 23, won team gold in addition to a floor exercise bronze after winning a team silver in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 217, \"to\": 319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9499810732130071, \"rank\": 0.05164193202869634, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As decorated as the two gymnasts are, both have decided they have unfinished business at the college level.\", \"from\": 321, \"to\": 428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Carey announced Wednesday in Corvallis, Ore. that she would return for her senior season at Oregon State.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 430, \"end\": 435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"score\": 0.9999999988294803, \"rank\": 1.1703850302237088e-09, \"text\": \"Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\"}, {\"begin\": 459, \"end\": 468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corvallis_Knights\", \"score\": 0.9901086203728581, \"rank\": 0.009990196452823685, \"text\": \"Corvallis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corvallis_Knights\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corvallis_Knights\"}, {\"begin\": 522, \"end\": 528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oregon\", \"score\": 0.7197058317163231, \"rank\": 0.38036401973419526, \"text\": \"Oregon\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oregon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oregon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m thrilled to announce that I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m committed to the 2025 season,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the five-time NCAA medalistsaidvia Nick Daschel ofThe Oregonianat a small celebration in her honor.\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 625, \"end\": 629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9984167386948667, \"rank\": 0.0015853410858863712, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 646, \"end\": 650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\", \"score\": 0.9958446890008431, \"rank\": 0.004172641373275962, \"text\": \"Nick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI look forward to continuing to compete, pushing my limits and striving for excellence with best team by my side.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  In an outtake fromThe Today Show, Chiles likewise announced she would compete collegiately for UCLA in '25.\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 927, \"end\": 931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"score\": 0.9998134603035982, \"rank\": 0.00018348557040245088, \"text\": \"UCLA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCLA_Bruins\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Our girl@chilesjordanhas a big announcement to make ... \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0091\\u0080\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00bc\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f@uclagymnasticsWe're so proud of you, Jordan!pic.twitter.com/vU0Cl8va4t  \\\"I am returning back to UCLA to represent the Bruins for my two remaining years of college,\\\" Chiles said.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 1185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1104, \"end\": 1108, \"